<HEAD>Iran Plans to Build New Cities</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> plans to build 12 new cities to house its soaring population, the official <ORGANIZATION> Islamic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Republic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agency </ORGANIZATION> reports. The agency, monitored in <LOCATION> Nicosia </LOCATION> on Monday, quoted Housing Minister <PERSON> Serajeddin </PERSON> <PERSON> Kazeroni </PERSON> as saying research was needed to develop construction methods so more people could own homes. <PERSON> Kazeroni </PERSON> was quoted as telling the daily newspaper Ettela'at that cheaper homes should be built that would consume less energy. <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>'s population has risen over the past decade from 33 to 50 million and is growing at the rate of 2.5 million annually.
