<HEAD>Emergency Plan To Reduce Smog in Santiago</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTIAGO, Chile (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The government has ordered a rotating shutdown of more than 130 factories and banned 50 percent of all buses from <LOCATION> Santiago </LOCATION>'s streets to reduce smog that has reached dangerous levels. Announcing the emergency measueres on Monday, Transport Minister <PERSON> Carlos </PERSON> <PERSON> Silva </PERSON> said the use of private and commercial cars in the capital also will be restricted with one out of five autos barred from the city streets daily. That restriction will be enforced according to the last digit on the license plates. <PERSON> Silva </PERSON> said some 130 Santiago-area factories found to be polluters will be required to shut down for 24 hours on a rotating basis, 50 factories at a time.
