<HEAD>Jury Hears Tape from Double Homicide</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHOENIX (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Jurors in the trial of a man charged with stabbing his wife to death heard a tape recording of the woman's plea for help, followed by her husband telling her she was `` bleeding just like a stuck hog.'' <PERSON> Alfred </PERSON> <PERSON> Lavers </PERSON>, 48, is charged with murder in the May 13, 1988, stabbing deaths of his wife, <PERSON> Mary </PERSON>, and 11-year-old stepdaughter, <PERSON> Jennifer </PERSON> <PERSON> Burns </PERSON>. The tape played Monday was found by police in a recorder under pillows in the stepdaughter's room. It contained a 90-minute recording of the domestic dispute that culminated in Mrs. <PERSON> Lavers </PERSON>' terrifying screams `` I'm dying,'' Mrs. <PERSON> Lavers </PERSON> was heard saying, just after she allegedly was stabbed by her husband. `` I know you are,'' he said. `` Please help me,'' she said. `` You're bleeding just like a stuck hog. I love you so much,'' he said. The victims' relatives sat fighting back emotion in the front row of the spectators' section as the tape was played. An elderly woman later identified as one of Mrs. <PERSON> Lavers </PERSON>' relatives broke down in tears and was led out. There was no discernible reaction by jurors, who followed the tape with a transcript. <PERSON> Lavers </PERSON>, 48, voluntarily removed himself from the <ORGANIZATION> Maricopa </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> County </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Superior </ORGANIZATION> courtroom while the tape was played. He returned for the defense portion of the case, in which public defender <PERSON> Roland </PERSON> <PERSON> Steinle </PERSON> called only one witness _ a police officer who said <PERSON> Lavers </PERSON> appeared `` out of it'' when he was arrested and booked. <PERSON> Steinle </PERSON> is attempting to show that <PERSON> Lavers </PERSON> was intoxicated when he stabbed the women, acted without premeditation and should be found guilty of a lesser crime. The trial resumes Wednesday.
