<HEAD>Lawsuit Over Broken Prom Date Settled Out of Court</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A high school sophomore who sued a boy for breaking their prom date wanted an apology but is settling for $ 81.28. <PERSON> Marlon </PERSON> <PERSON> Shadd </PERSON>, 17, agreed to reimburse <PERSON> Tomontra </PERSON> <PERSON> Mangrum </PERSON>, 15, for her prom expenses, including shoes and a hairdo, and the costs of her lawsuit. `` It's just stupid,'' <PERSON> Shadd </PERSON> said Monday. `` She's just freaking out. I do n't know what's wrong with her.'' `` We said we'll pay, just to get rid of it,'' said <PERSON> Shadd </PERSON>'s attorney, <PERSON> Joel </PERSON> <PERSON> Daves </PERSON> <PERSON> III </PERSON> <PERSON> Shadd </PERSON>, who plans to attend <ORGANIZATION> Kansas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> State </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> on a basketball scholarship, maintains he called Ms. <PERSON> Mangrum </PERSON> a week before the prom to say he had hurt his ankle and would not be able to escort her. `` She just did n't believe me,'' <PERSON> Shadd </PERSON> said. `` She thought I was kidding around.'' <PERSON> Shadd </PERSON> and Ms. <PERSON> Mangrum </PERSON> have not spoken since the suit was filed, said <PERSON> Valerie </PERSON> <PERSON> Mangrum </PERSON>, <PERSON> Tomontra </PERSON>'s mother. `` He has refused to apologize to her, but she felt like the check was apology enough,'' the mother said.
