<HEAD>Leaning Tower of Providence Immortalized on T-Shirts</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The building that twice has defied explosions to fell it, now is being immortalized in three T-shirt designs and their creators are in a spat over whose brainstorm the shirt idea was. One depicts `` The Leaning Tower of <LOCATION> Providence </LOCATION>,'' another `` The Leaning Tower of <LOCATION> Bilray </LOCATION>,'' for the construction company that pulled the boo-boo, and `` The Hartford Park Horror Project,'' sponsored by Republicans who want to make political capital from the snafu. Bilray, contracted by the <ORGANIZATION> Providence </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Housing </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Authority </ORGANIZATION>, tried twice on May 21 to implode the <LOCATION> Hartford </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Park </LOCATION> housing project and succeeded only in knocking out one floor, leaving the L-shaped building leaning on itself. The company has since been working at taking the building down with a traditional wrecking ball. State <ORGANIZATION> GOP </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Vallante </PERSON> came out with the Republican T-shirt on Monday, but he says he had the idea all along but just got sidetracked about getting the shirts made up. The housing authority sold out its first 100 shirts Thursday and says it has 300 more going on sale Tuesday, with a price increase from $ 4 to $ 6. When <PERSON> Bilray </PERSON> groused they already had $ 9 shirts for sale, <PERSON> Stephen </PERSON> <PERSON> O'Rourke </PERSON>, the authority's director, said he was the one who came up with the phrase `` Leaning Tower of Bilray'' the day the implosion failed. `` What does he want to do, sue us?'' <PERSON> O'Rourke </PERSON> said. `` I mean this is not one of those things that is high up on my agenda.'' <PERSON> Vallante </PERSON> said the <ORGANIZATION> GOP </ORGANIZATION> would offer to eventually add the total cost of the project to the back of its $ 5 shirts. `` The people of <LOCATION> Providence </LOCATION> have a right to know what is the cost in extra security, the costs for safety, the cost of the lost business in the area for this tower that is a testament to incompetence,'' <PERSON> Vallante </PERSON> said.
