<HEAD>House, Senate Panels Differ on Pace of Legislation</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By DIANE DUSTON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> member whose subcommittee is crafting rural development legislation says he wants to move slowly but surely, despite the desire in the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> to push such a measure through quickly. `` We're taking a different approach,'' said Rep. <PERSON> Glenn </PERSON> English, <LOCATION> D-Okla </LOCATION>., whose subcommittee is holding a lengthy series of hearings before crafting legislation early this fall `` We're reaching outside <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>,'' said English. `` We will have heard from over 40 witnesses by the time we finish hearings this month.'' He also has scheduled hearings in five regions of the country in August. English said the House Agriculture subcommittee on conservation, credit and rural development is moving as quickly as it can, but he does n't understand the `` push it through approach'' being taken by the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION>. Sen. <PERSON> Patrick </PERSON> <PERSON> Leahy </PERSON>, D-Vt. and chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agriculture </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION>, was joined by several other <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> senators, the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Development </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Organizations </ORGANIZATION> and the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Counties </ORGANIZATION> at a news conference Tuesday promoting his bill `` One of the reasons we worked so hard to get this out is so that it wo n't be perceived as a farm bill,'' said <PERSON> Leahy </PERSON>. `` Ninety percent of rural <LOCATION> America </LOCATION> is not involved in farming.'' English said that timing will determine whether the legislation is incorporated into the 1990 omnibus bil