<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 Here is a chronology of events in the takeover battle for <ORGANIZATION> NWA </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, parent of <ORGANIZATION> Northwest </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION>: March 28 _ After months of takeover rumors, <ORGANIZATION> NWA </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> Steven </PERSON> <PERSON> Rothmeier </PERSON> announces that an unnamed investment group has accumulated 4.9 percent of the company's stock and approached <ORGANIZATION> NWA </ORGANIZATION> about a possible acquisition. <PERSON> Rothmeier </PERSON> later identifies the suitor as a friendly group led by <PERSON> Alfred </PERSON> <PERSON> Checchi </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION>. March 30 _ Oil billionaire <PERSON> Marvin </PERSON> <PERSON> Davis </PERSON> offers $ 2.67 billion, or $ 90 a share, to buy <ORGANIZATION> NWA </ORGANIZATION>. April 20 _ <PERSON> Davis </PERSON> launches hostile $ 70 a share tender offer after the <ORGANIZATION> NWA </ORGANIZATION> board rejects his buyout proposal. The board later advises shareholders not to sell to <PERSON> Davis </PERSON>. May 9 _ <ORGANIZATION> Pan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Am </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>. Chairman <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> <PERSON> Plaskett </PERSON> announces his company's interest in acquiring <ORGANIZATION> Northwest </ORGANIZATION> May 15 _ <ORGANIZATION> NWA </ORGANIZATION> holds its annual meeting in relative quiet after <PERSON> Davis </PERSON> drops his threatened proxy fight to gain control of the board of directors in order to join the formal bidding process outlined by <ORGANIZATION> NWA </ORGANIZATION>'s board. May 30 _ <PERSON> Davis </PERSON>, <PERSON> Checchi </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Pan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Am </ORGANIZATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Machinists </ORGANIZATION>, and