<FIRST>r f PM-InterestRateOptions     06-20 0298</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Interest Rate Options,0307</SECOND>
<HEAD>SEC Okays Interest Rate Options Trading</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Options </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> says it has received approval from the <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> to trade options on interest rates and will launch the new products on Friday. Exchange officials say options on interest rates will eliminate the inverse price-to-rate relationship associated with other <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> bond, <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> bill and <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> note markets and should appeal to individual investors. `` For the first time, there will be a product based on the level of interest rates themselves,'' <ORGANIZATION> CBOE </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> Duke </PERSON> <PERSON> Chapman </PERSON> said in a news release issued Monday. An option is a right to buy or sell a financial instrument or commodity at a specified price by a given date. Investors can use options to hedge their positions in cash markets or to speculate on market movements. The <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Options </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> is the world's largest options market. The exchange said in it will offer options on both short-term and long-term interest rates. The option on short-term rates will be based on the yield of the most recently auctioned 13-week Treasury bill. The option on long-term rates will be based on the average yield-to-maturity of the two most recently auctioned 7-and 10-year <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> notes and 30-year <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> bonds. Unlike other interest-rate instruments, the price of these products is based on a composite that is calculated using interest-rate yields rather than the prices of bonds or bills. The prices of other interest-rate products move in the opposite direction from the products' yields. But with the new options on interest rates, prices will move in tandem with interest rates. The <ORGANIZATION> CBOE </ORGANIZATION> also lists options on 201 widely traded stocks, on the <ORGANIZATION> Standard </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Poor's 100 and 500 stock indexes and on <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> bonds and notes.
</TEXT>
