<BYLINE>By IKE FLORES</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Harcourt </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Brace </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Jovanovich </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> put its four Sea World parks and two other attractions on the market Tuesday to help extricate itself from a $ 2.5 billion debt brought on by a 1987 hostile takeover attempt. The company said selling the marine parks in <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ohio </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Boardwalk </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Baseball and <ORGANIZATION> Cypress </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Gardens </ORGANIZATION> in central <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> was the best way to meet debt obligations and concentrate on its publishing and insurance divisions. Estimates of the value of the properties ranged from $ 1 billion to $ 2.5 billion. Wall Street applauded the move. <ORGANIZATION> HBJ </ORGANIZATION>'s stock closed up $ 3.75 a share Tuesday to $ 13.87 -LCB- in active trading on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>. `` It's a positive development for the company because of its weak balance sheet,'' said <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Dunlap </PERSON>, a securities analyst with <ORGANIZATION> Brown </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Brothers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Harriman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>. `` Clearly, something had to be done.'' <PERSON> Elizabeth </PERSON> <PERSON> Bramwell </PERSON>, of the <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> firm <ORGANIZATION> Gabelli </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, said <ORGANIZATION> HBJ </ORGANIZATION> `` should n't have been doing all these -LRB- other -RRB- things. The first love of this company is publishing.'' <ORGANIZATION> HBJ </ORGANIZATION>, the nation's largest textbook publisher, has struggled with a $ 2.9 billion recapitalization program over the past two years by disposing of trade-magazine and school-supply interests, streamlining its parks division and reshuffling its publishing operations _ all of which included huge reductions in personnel. <ORGANIZATION> HBJ </ORGANIZATION> restructured its operations, through bank loans and high-risk junk bonds, to fend off a hostile takeover attempt by British publisher <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Maxwell </PERSON> in 1987. The decision to sell the theme parks and real estate holdings followed recent talks between <ORGANIZATION> HBJ </ORGANIZATION>'s longtime chairman, <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Jovanovich </PERSON>, and the company's new president, <PERSON> Ralph </PERSON> <PERSON> D. </PERSON> <PERSON> Caulo </PERSON>, according to a three-paragraph statement by <ORGANIZATION> HBJ </ORGANIZATION>. `` The <ORGANIZATION> HBJ </ORGANIZATION> directors have authorized this sale, which is subject to the approval of <ORGANIZATION> HBJ </ORGANIZATION>'s lenders,'' the announcement said. It added that <PERSON> Caulo </PERSON> `` is prepared to leave <ORGANIZATION> HBJ </ORGANIZATION> in order to manage these businesses under new ownership.'' The parks will be sold as a package to an investor that `` wants to invest in them and continue to see them grow,'' <PERSON> Bob </PERSON> <PERSON> Evanson </PERSON>, head of the theme parks division, said in an interview. <PERSON> Evanson </PERSON> said the company had spoken to `` quite a few'' potential buyers of the parks, which brought in an estimated $ 388 million in revenue last year, and a separate tract of land near <LOCATION> Orlando </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Interna