<HEAD>ABC, PR Newswire, Broadcast Company Announce Joint Venture</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SUNNYVALE, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> ABC-TV </ORGANIZATION>, PR Newswire and the Indesys data broadcast company announced the formation Tuesday of a joint-venture wire service to transmit news to entertainment and television editors and writers throughout the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Canada </LOCATION>. The high-speed wire will feature program changes, production schedules and the latest news from major broadcast and cable networks, movie and TV production companies, publishing houses, record companies, concert tour organizers and other entertainment sources. The system `` will provide news sources with a fast, reliable and direct link to the entertainment media,'' said <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Steinberg </PERSON>, president of PR Newswire. `` The latest news from <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Hollywood </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Nashville </LOCATION> and overseas will be on editors' desks around the country within minutes of its release.'' Information will be transmitted over an FM subcarrier and a satellite information distribution network to multiple receivers. <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>, a subsidiary of <ORGANIZATION> Capital </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cities-ABC </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, is the first major broadcasting network to participate in the wire. `` As our business is increasingly affected by new technologies, we have looked for more efficient and expeditious means to distribute information about our company,'' said <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Connelly </PERSON>, an <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> spokesman.
