<HEAD>Legal Fight Between Home Shopping Network, GTE Goes To Trial</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: INSERTS 4 grafs after 8th graf pvs, `GTE Florida ...,' to UPDATE
with GTE statement to jury. Picks up 9th graf pvs, `HSN's original ...'</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By PAT LEISNER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>CLEARWATER, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Home Shopping Network lost $ 400 million in profits because its telephone equipment was inadequate to handle the volume of calls, an attorney said Tuesday. The hefty loss was suffered over a 14-month period as the St. Petersburg-based television retail giant went through a huge spurt of growth, <PERSON> Chet </PERSON> <PERSON> Kamin </PERSON>, a lawyer for <ORGANIZATION> HSN </ORGANIZATION>, told a jury. <ORGANIZATION> GTE </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> and its subsidiaries knew about the problems _ that a staggering number of calls were not getting through _ but lied to the company and persuaded <ORGANIZATION> HSN </ORGANIZATION> instead to buy even more equipment to try to resolve the dilemma, he said. `` Home Shopping's like Mother's Day, every day,'' said <PERSON> Kamin </PERSON>, referring to the high number of calls from viewers who may only purchase items while they are being displayed on the screen. `` What happened as a result of <ORGANIZATION> GTE </ORGANIZATION> blocking calls and not telling us is that we lost millions and millions of calls,'' <PERSON> Kamin </PERSON> said in opening statements. A jury of five women and one man was seated Tuesday in a $ 1.5 billion battle between the corporate giants, <ORGANIZATION> HSN </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> GTE </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> HSN </ORGANIZATION> sued <ORGANIZATION> GTE </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Florida </ORGANIZATION>, its parent <ORGANIZATION> GTE </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, and other subsidaries in 1987, alleging a number of misdeeds linked to what it claimed was inadequate service and faulty phone equipment <ORGANIZATION> GTE </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Florida </ORGANIZATION> and its parent company, a multibillion-dollar telecommunications firm based in <LOCATION> Stamford </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Conn. </LOCATION>, have denied any wrongdoing and said there was nothing wrong with their equipment. They filed a countersuit alleging slander and libel and claimed that <ORGANIZATION> HSN </ORGANIZATION> executives engaged in a `` blame the telephone company scheme to mask <ORGANIZATION> HSN </ORGANIZATION>'s poor market and financial performance ...'' <ORGANIZATION> GTE </ORGANIZATION> counsel <PERSON> Roy </PERSON> <PERSON> Reardon </PERSON> told the jury that <ORGANIZATION> HSN </ORGANIZATION>'s charges were `` absolutely baseless.'' <ORGANIZATION> HSN </ORGANIZATION> had 4 million subscribers when it talked to <ORGANIZATION> GTE </ORGANIZATION> about telephone service in 1985, <PERSON> Reardon </PERSON> said. That grew to 9 million by August 1986, and one year later the number skyrocketed to 46.5 million, he said. Sales soared from $ 11 million in 1985 to $ 582 million by August 1987 _ all with the <ORGANIZATION> GTE </ORGANIZATION> telephone network in place, he said. `` We do n't believe you just cover your own problems of mismanagement ... by blaming other people. There was no fraud ... no coverup,'' <PERSON> Reardon </PERSON> said. <ORGANIZATION> HSN </ORGANIZATION>'s original 12-count complaint has been reduced to four charges _ fraud, negligent misrepresentation, breach of trust and confidence and breach of fiduciary duty. Pinellas Circuit Judge <PERSON> Howard </PERSON> <PERSON> Rives </PERSON> combined both suits in what is expected to be a six-week trial. Although there are no phone company records showing the precise number of calls in question, Home Shopping expects to show evidence that 42 million calls were not completed betweeen February 1986 and April 1987, <PERSON> Kamin </PERSON> said. He added that not all lost calls would have translated into sales. <PERSON> Kamin </PERSON> presented what he said was an internal <ORGANIZATION> GTE </ORGANIZATION> memo that noted as many as 26,000 overflow calls in a one-hour period. The in-house document asks what are <ORGANIZATION> GTE </ORGANIZATION> subsidiaries responsibilities to the customer and the efficiency of his service, and notes that <ORGANIZATION> HSN </ORGANIZATION> `` is not aware that its calls are restricted.'' `` It was in a sense a disaster waiting to happen,'' <PERSON> Kamin </PERSON> told the six-member jury and five alternates. After April 1987 surveys showed <ORGANIZATION> HSN </ORGANIZATION> was losing 50 percent of its calls the company switched carriers to <ORGANIZATION> MCI </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communications </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Kamin </PERSON> said, adding the call completion rate now is over 90 percent.
